================================================================================
Modifications
================================================================================

Portions of this library have been modified for the MTBART project.
Modifications Copyright (C) 2025 Jungang Zou.
Modifications are licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0.

The following files contain modifications (each file's header documents
its own changes in detail):

  misc/mcmc_structs.hpp
    - Added persistent dual-averaging adaptation fields to nuts_settings_t
      (use_persistent_adapt, epsilon_bar_persist, h_val_persist,
       mu_val_persist, adapt_iter_persist).

  mcmc/nuts.hpp
    - Added a persistent / mini-warmup adaptation mode for the NUTS dual
      averaging step-size scheme, so the step size can be adapted over
      short warmups inside an outer Gibbs loop and warm-started from the
      previously adapted epsilon_bar.

  mcmc/nuts.ipp
    - Added an overflow / underflow guard (max 50 doublings and clamping
      of step_size to [1e-10, 1e10]) inside nuts_find_initial_step_size
      to prevent infinite loops / NaN step sizes under extreme curvature.

All other files in this directory are unmodified from upstream MCMClib.
